Figure 9.7
 shows the comparison of polish rates of Cu in abrasive-free and abrasive-containing (3wt% colloidal silica, ∼50nm) solutions of 0.065mol/dm3 OA+5wt% H2O2 as a function of pH. The polish rates with and without the abrasive particles were similar at pH≥3, but the rates were significantly different in the presence and absence of abrasive at lower pH values. Such a removal rate dependence on pH and the abrasive's effects was clearly explained by the open-circuit potential (OCP) data under polishing and no polishing conditions (Figure 9.8
).
